==English==
===Etymology===
From Greek ''[[φωνη]]'' (''phone'') meaning "sound" and ''[[γραφη]]'' (''graphe'') meaning "write"

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
''a'' '''phonograph'''

# A [[device]] that [[capture]]s [[sound wave]]s onto an [[engraved]] [[archive]]; a [[lathe]].
# (''Commonwealth'') A device that [[reproduce]]s sound from [[cylinder]] [[records]].
# (''U.S.'') A [[turntable]], especially an [[early]], [[archaic]] [[record player]].

